What is List<>?
° List<> is an interface in Java’s Collections Framework.
° It defines an ordered collection (sequence) of elements.
° Allows duplicates and maintains insertion order.

Key Features of List<> Interface
° Order is maintained > elements stay in the order they were
added.
° Duplicates allowed > can contain multiple identical elements.
° Index-based access > elements can be accessed using indices.

ArrayList<> - Overview
° Backed by a resizable array.
° Fast random access (O(1)) > direct indexing.
° Adding/removing at the end is fast (O(1)), but slow at the
start/middle (O(n)) due to shifting elements.

LinkedList<> - Overview
° Uses doubly linked nodes > each node points to the next and
previous.
° Fast insertions/removals at start/middle (O(1)) because no
shifting is required.
° Slow random access (O(n)) > traversal needed to find elements.
